Deviations from DESIGN.md
=========================

NOTE — DESIGN.md proposed a separate `electron/spotify/poller.ts`-resident interval
loop combined with module-level `startPoller`/`stopPoller` glue. We kept those module
exports (so main.ts can wire focus/blur/visibility hooks the way the design specifies)
but added a `createPoller(deps)` factory that returns the actual handle, and an
`attachPoller()` hook that the IPC layer calls once it has built the OAuth + client.
This split keeps the pure helpers (`cadenceFor`, `mapPlaybackResponse`) trivially
testable and decouples poller state from the singleton lifecycle. No behavioral change.

NOTE — DESIGN.md §"Public API / surface" listed `auth.getToken` as a debug-only IPC
channel. Implementation also exposes `auth.getStatus` (returns logged-in / logged-out)
because the renderer's first paint needs to know which screen to show before the
first `auth:changed` event fires. `getStatus` reads in-memory AuthState plus the
keytar entry as a fallback so a freshly-launched app with a saved refresh token
boots straight to the Dashboard. Negligible attack surface (returns a boolean kind).

NOTE — Loopback redirect URI fixed to port **53682** (rclone convention) per the
implement-stage instructions, rather than DESIGN.md's "ephemeral port" wording. This
is required so the user can register a single redirect URI in the Spotify dev
dashboard. `runLoopback()` still accepts `port` as a parameter so tests can pass
`port: 0` for ephemeral binding.

NOTE — `keytar` installed and built natively on this Intel Mac (Xcode CLT present).
The fallback JSON-file path documented in `electron/auth/keychain.ts` is wired but
not exercised — kept as a defensive branch so a future packaging environment without
the prebuilt binary doesn't soft-brick auth.

